Name: Bleecker Street Bar
reviews:
[{'author_name': 'Robert Forehand', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103129126507736055239/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgB3y-YS5EgdYlpJy0KibTpUdWTiilnu2NWx9OpnQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '2 years ago', 'text': "Great Bar/hangout.  only complaint is they don't serve any snacks/food.  They don't claim to and this is a true bar....just go for enjoying atmosphere and great drinks!", 'time': 1583865806}, {'author_name': 'Karen Loizou', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/118107934323622157206/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AATXAJwWWCzawhuXJ3aCoOxB_ibTlRdnO92nq7zyIL_0=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 years ago', 'text': 'Great place. My friend and I were exploring the local area during a trip over from the UK to celebrate her 50th. On her birthday we came across this bar by accident. It was a freezing cold and wet day and we were made to feel welcome as soon as we sat down at the bar. The bartender was extremely friendly and we had a lot of laughs with her as she shared stories about herself and her bar in Brooklyn. She was incredibly friendly and polite and swiftly served all the customers who arrived after us. We have great memories of our two hours in this place and really enjoyed it.', 'time': 1581707123}, {'author_name': 'Rowan Pritchard', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111504804483361724996/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gh1gxBJbQXxIze3-PbPo0Vc-bNSu8dl-IOq6H-fkPQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6', 'rating': 2, 'relative_time_description': '2 years ago', 'text': "This should be a great bar but the service is terrible. The bar staff prefer to clean up and chat rather than serve, and the bar hand refuses to serve but then stands around doing nothing.
Aside from this bad service it's a nice bar with great pool tables out back.", 'time': 1577723649}, {'author_name': 'Shana Urban', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101532461588137535154/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhHhp_m2BjsX1LAVS-NYa1B4mcQ9oP2OWT8ICq0Xio=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 years ago', 'text': 'Best bar in the area! Pool & darts, great drinks & cool bartenders (Pete is the man!) Will be back for sure :D', 'time': 1573108972}, {'author_name': 'Ryan Lindquist', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108447259543144191918/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AATXAJwBisKFIujRQte4tDrLXNedKDrbAwr1i3V7NbR1=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 2, 'relative_time_description': '2 years ago', 'text': 'Teenagers not welcome...

Nice local place - good taps and good vibe, but possibly not good for tourists or families.

Mid-afternoon, we came in after some tourist fun in NYC. My wife, youngest (6) and I ordered drinks (chips for the kid). 30 minutes in, our oldest two came in (14 & 16) - they were not allowed as they were too close to drinking age....sad, really.', 'time': 1571345299}]

Name: Nassau Bar
reviews: [{'author_name': 'Al Golzari', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102641063392588875134/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gj9XpxnQH9E2cFgM9p_o0hvkRWFCFGvFXHl91c=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 weeks ago', 'text': "Been living in the neighborhood since 2006 and found this little gem back in 2016 walking by one day.  Have no idea how I spent my first 10 years here not knowing about it.  Used to go now and again in 2016 and started coming back in 2021.  If you're a fan of down-to-earth dive bars that aren't pretentious, this is probably the bar for you.  The bartenders, day and night, are super friendly and definitely a sight for sore eyes.  I'm sorry to have seen a few awesome bartenders like Gigi leave but Phil, Kate, Vicki, Haley, Natalie, Grace are really great.  The owner is also a really nice guy and a lot more generous than other bars in the neighborhood.  My only complaints are that I wish there was one little signature snack that you can buy there (that they would bring from the outside)...like a soft pretzel or something.  But they allow outside food.  And I do wish that the tonic water had more bubbles and tasted a little fresher (sorry John).  But aside from those minor issues, this has become a great regular spot that I feel very welcomed at.  For those who may feel the way I used to...it can be a bit intimidating at first; I understand that.  But just start going and get to know everyone and you'll be fine.", 'time': 1654882146}, {'author_name': 'Da Saint Da Canis', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117103068647604819249/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gjni06guCs3aRlOy1s5_x56DeBSf4cFpWAFHdMGDFk=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 weeks ago', 'text': 'And amazing place to sit back drink listen to music or watch the game...', 'time': 1654719113}, {'author_name': 'Alexis Mccarthy', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112571315058061412799/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiB3No-AGrqlYpj-_SSMyvn_VCTUu4iZp2ctYFq=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '2 months ago', 'text': "This was the first time I saw a bar with ping pong tables! Totally cute and fun. We didn't actually try the food though. We just drank and played some ping pong.", 'time': 1648701645}, {'author_name': 'Nick P', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113607567439595584708/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AATXAJw40ozUVSVeYbG95ByVL3o22BXbAUkO70fP4mql=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 months ago', 'text': 'One of the best dive bars downtown. Great place.', 'time': 1649199716}, {'author_name': 'Tony Swag', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106762390017780153294/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhH-FcDKiT0Zi0rZ_LkvhXWsTuRAfDOZoCaVyYGew=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': "LIT's are $25 but the overall vibe and energy my bartender had was 🔥🔥🔥 The owner also came thru with a free round for everyone at the bar. I wanted so much to like this place. The environment is elegant and beautiful and the staff was polite and attentive. Unfortunately that\'s the extent of the positive things I can say about the experience. At $30-$45 per cocktail, I was really expecting premium ingredients and an impressive presentation for the cocktails but The Bar at Baccarat just didn\'t deliver on either of these measures. The drinks tasted okay but they were not much different than what you can get at any other halfway decent cocktail bar. And despite the description on the menu promising "a smoke show" or other interesting presentations, our drinks arrived with very little presentation or flair. Have a question about the ingredients or the flavor profile for any of their signature drinks?  Well, you\'re out of luck because (in our case) our server had not tasted any of the cocktails on the menu so he couldn\'t offer guidance or recommendations.   As my Texas friends would say, The Bar at Baccarat is "all hat and no cattle". The FRIES are really tasty 🤤', 'time': 1629421397}, {'author_name': 'Darren Austin', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102364141052700535896/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhHv9kYzD7QMpSchwiWir3uSXKRysYLyFpwdam1PgI=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 2, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'Disappointing. I wanted so much to like this place. The environment is elegant and beautiful and the staff was polite and attentive. Unfortunately that\'s the extent of the positive things I can say about the experience. At $30-$45 per cocktail, I was really expecting premium ingredients and an impressive presentation for the cocktails but The Bar at Baccarat just didn\'t deliver on either of these measures. The drinks tasted okay but they were not much different than what you can get at any other halfway decent cocktail bar. And despite the description on the menu promising "a smoke show" or other interesting presentations, our drinks arrived with very little presentation or flair. Have a question about the ingredients or the flavor profile for any of their signature drinks?  Well, you\'re out of luck because (in our case) our server had not tasted any of the cocktails on the menu so he couldn\'t offer guidance or recommendations.   As my Texas friends would say, The Bar at Baccarat is "all hat and no cattle". reviews: [{'author_name': 'sobeefy1', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/118380925373526406984/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AATXAJwYODyq3n5NrHsFhR_y8SbGFV0x8yu83mHmVb7g=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '4 months ago', 'text': 'Wow just wow. We had the French onion soup, the chorizo appetizer, the pork sliders, the beef tips, the carrots, and cheesecake for dessert everything was delicious. Name: New Paltz Brewing Company (Pfälzerbräu)
reviews: [{'author_name': 'richard bach', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113931682176593605320/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AATXAJyoU-ueMl5WpUl3ZqNMSCVpxM-BCyU8wanrIn2c=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 years ago', 'text': 'I’ve been to many breweries in The NY NJ area. I thought I was drinking some good beers and there are some good ones. New Paltz Brewing however has changed my perspective on what a beer should be. Focusing specifically on German style brews, you can taste the passion and authenticity that goes into each style. The brewmaster is friendly and excited to talk to anyone about his craft in a laid back down-to-earth atmosphere. If you like mass produced yellow beers then this is probably not the place for you. Are you ready to transform your palate to a higher plateau? My friend, you found the place.', 'time': 1570978601}, {'author_name': 'Giovani M', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100783569618224403944/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AATXAJykmD7c_B_tWNSHQd5ns1SqKuFYtFnxuXQyF83q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 years ago', 'text': 'I like to go with friends to this restaurant with my highest recommendations. Pros:
- Patrick, the server, was very friendly and kind. We enjoyed his amiability. All the staff were very nice to us and our 1 year old!
- Nice decor and ambiance
- Vast and extensive menu, I want to try so many things!

Cons:
- Food took a long time. I get it with staffing issues everywhere. Nonetheless, this affects the dining experience
- 2lbs of mussels - was good. Not the best. Not the worst. It came with whole wheat toast. I think better if it came with fries.
- 10 oz ribeye - sauce was too sweet. The specific cut we received was not great. Lots of tough pieces.
- scallops, octopus, wild boar belly on chickpeas dish - I liked this dish and really want to like it more. I loved that it was all protein. The base/sauce was slightly too tomato-y and slightly acidic.

For the reputation and reviews I expected slightly more. Some people come dressed, some don’t. It seems like people come here to eat and grab a drink before a night out. Average tab for drinks is about $80 which isn’t so bad. They also have a decent selection of liquor for those who don’t really drink beer. Average price for cocktails. reviews:
[{'author_name': 'Danielly Ribeiro', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104158325776054523846/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhFB1MJ4jck4dAgvRqk8rBuFagDbRGXq0so_iXsJg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a week ago', 'text': 'Best breakfast burrito ever! The place is very cute inside and has a cool vibe. Service is good as well. Totally recommend. :)', 'time': 1655733673}, {'author_name': 'Bryan Lau', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106783065927371073823/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhufTQi-8R9KK9bDorL156dgzzl0pxDayWoBJwgZeE=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a week ago', 'text': 'Reasonably priced drinks and pretty good value for food!

The bacon wrapped dates were decadent with the fat and richness balanced by the sweet dates and maple syrup.

Eggplant dip was salty. Couldn’t taste the eggplant. The fresh pitas were amazing though!

Jerk chicken had notes of rice vinegar and ginger. Great flavor when paired with the ranch. Everything our group ordered was good, if not great.

Copy of a Copy, Sowing Season, and Whirlybird were the individual favorites from our rounds. Assemble the Empire was on the sweet side, but good for people that would enjoy something berry forward. Normally I take photos to throw into the Google Review, but I was so preoccupied with enjoy the vibe and drinks, that I completely forgot! The fact that this place completely kicked me into relaxation mode from the start is a plus.

I'd definitely recommend this bar if you're looking for solid cocktails in the area.", 'time': 1655683041}, {'author_name': 'Steven Jackson', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109095059168433633730/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiL0cLfTyw96ttsIZzNyF_Rjah3CIJilCcb__P7wQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '3 weeks ago', 'text': "This place is a great black to have a bite and a drink..... the burger here is AMAZING! Then when I asked for my bill they charged me for both my drinks, not just one because they already charged me for one. When I told them they flat out denied it without checking or caring. I then had to suggest I could show them the charge, they talked to me as if I was picking a problem with them instead of them addressing an issues they completely gaslighted me and said that’s not possible and not ONCE apologized and even said “I don’t get anything out of this.” Then why were they so defensive instead of apologizing like a normal person? When talking to each other they simply said “it’s not possible.” As if I were still making this up.

I was charged $14 for one drink while I was sitting down then $28 for both drinks when I got the bill.

BE CAREFUL SCAMMERS charging you for drinks before you get your bill for some drinks then giving you the full bill. Scam scam scam

And they were so polite and warm to everyone else and so indifferent and cold to me, I noticed the difference immediately. If they’re rude to you, you’re probably the next target. Maybe because I asked them to change the sports channel. I smiled to them the entire time until they gaslit me at the end.', 'time': 1649798094}]

It's dark, the music doesn't attempt to be trendy, the beers are well priced, and it isn't incredibly hip or packed.

There is a clear sense of identity that isn't afraid to just be.', 'time': 1650435356}, {'author_name': 'John S', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107306153832117687228/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AATXAJz8h4yuiJQW5uY_CVTWauBnJN5P1q_Gc9UeVcUZ9A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '3 months ago', 'text': 'Great spot. Cheap as hell and no frillies. They have 24 oz cans of Busch.', 'time': 1648475859}, {'author_name': 'John Love', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116084523823728840319/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjTCwmOCwKsEfEbcXKRMj_QPE5ebfzEtQT4bpm-fg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '3 months ago', 'text': 'A friend and I seeked out an unpretentious place to drink and hang out. Bourgeoise be damned!

One Star's self-proclamation as a "...dingy hole.\xa0On a deadish street. With cans instead of bottles..." Sounded perfect.

And it was.

We started with a "High Beam". A 'special' listed on the chalkboard on the wall. A shot of Jim Beam and a tall can Miller High Life ("The Champagne Of Beers") ($9).

Perfect.

A happy surprise was the handful of actual taps rather than every beer being in cans. A sample of a craft porter revealed a fine brew.

Joe the bartender was attentive, friendly, talkative when it became apparent that that was what we were looking for.

As my friend said, and I entirely agree:

Joe is a 6-star bartender in a 5-star bar with a 1-star moniker. Thanks for the amazing evening , Joe!

--> The dudes from Seattle.', 'time': 1648095449}, {'author_name': 'Karthik Nagarajan', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100792881447145419590/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjV-kbQdt36gWYqtrYjYR1Lc80r-XL4Xl3OwXS3VGU=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 months ago', 'text': "It's exactly as advertised. Best quiet dive in the neighborhood.", 'time': 1649805746}]

Name: Hidden Lane Bar
reviews:
[{'author_name': 'Elizabeth', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113168621361652514393/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AATXAJwPWYYNGNW-SH0R6oKy1SB6G2eNjEgAJoLTVq6w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 weeks ago', 'text': 'A non profit I am on the board of was seeking a happy hour space for our first in-person event in over two years. He went above and beyond to make sure everything ran smoothly. The bartenders were able to make specialty cocktails that our organization had pre-selected which were a big hit. The feedback from attendees regarding the space and venue were superb. The event was such a success and we are so thankful to Hidden Lane! Name: Nassau Bar
reviews: [{'author_name': 'Al Golzari', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102641063392588875134/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gj9XpxnQH9E2cFgM9p_o0hvkRWFCFGvFXHl91c=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 weeks ago', 'text': "Been living in the neighborhood since 2006 and found this little gem back in 2016 walking by one day.  Have no idea how I spent my first 10 years here not knowing about it.  Used to go now and again in 2016 and started coming back in 2021.  If you're a fan of down-to-earth dive bars that aren't pretentious, this is probably the bar for you.  The bartenders, day and night, are super friendly and definitely a sight for sore eyes.  I'm sorry to have seen a few awesome bartenders like Gigi leave but Phil, Kate, Vicki, Haley, Natalie, Grace are really great.  The owner is also a really nice guy and a lot more generous than other bars in the neighborhood.  My only complaints are that I wish there was one little signature snack that you can buy there (that they would bring from the outside)...like a soft pretzel or something.  But they allow outside food.  And I do wish that the tonic water had more bubbles and tasted a little fresher (sorry John).  But aside from those minor issues, this has become a great regular spot that I feel very welcomed at.  For those who may feel the way I used to...it can be a bit intimidating at first; I understand that.  But just start going and get to know everyone and you'll be fine.", 'time': 1654882146}, {'author_name': 'Da Saint Da Canis', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117103068647604819249/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gjni06guCs3aRlOy1s5_x56DeBSf4cFpWAFHdMGDFk=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 weeks ago', 'text': 'And amazing place to sit back drink listen to music or watch the game...', 'time': 1654719113}, {'author_name': 'Alexis Mccarthy', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112571315058061412799/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiB3No-AGrqlYpj-_SSMyvn_VCTUu4iZp2ctYFq=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '2 months ago', 'text': "This was the first time I saw a bar with ping pong tables! I wanted so much to like this place. The environment is elegant and beautiful and the staff was polite and attentive. Unfortunately that\'s the extent of the positive things I can say about the experience. At $30-$45 per cocktail, I was really expecting premium ingredients and an impressive presentation for the cocktails but The Bar at Baccarat just didn\'t deliver on either of these measures. The drinks tasted okay but they were not much different than what you can get at any other halfway decent cocktail bar. And despite the description on the menu promising "a smoke show" or other interesting presentations, our drinks arrived with very little presentation or flair. Have a question about the ingredients or the flavor profile for any of their signature drinks?  Well, you\'re out of luck because (in our case) our server had not tasted any of the cocktails on the menu so he couldn\'t offer guidance or recommendations.   As my Texas friends would say, The Bar at Baccarat is "all hat and no cattle".  Save your money and skip this place.', 'time': 1636090475}, {'author_name': 'David Borghard', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106993731337853236579/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AATXAJxSVPZIVl4tvVqW42WbUawA159u0RYWqjVYmzhvNA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '6 months ago', 'text': "What a wonderful and special experience coming to this place. reviews: [{'author_name': 'Naresh Hinduja', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116040122370016978788/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhUeCIhOyZJ4xhr9We0-PPlqPzPsODZ7fIh5y2LMA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': '2 months ago', 'text': 'So I go through a lot of reviews saying their locals that go here etc. Good food, everybody\'s friendly etc. So I figured I\'d give it a try. I go in there. I ask for a somewhat expensive tequila bartender said it\'s $ 11.50 and I said that\'s fine because I understand it\'s that expensive. What I did not understand is after getting a small glass full of ice which was less than half full of the tequila that I paid $11.50 for made no sense. First of all, the glass is small So it stands to normal logical reasoning that after you fill ice if you put even just one full of shot, it should at least be half full. This was not even half full so I realized the bartender was just short-changing me now for a new customer that goes in and is willing to try a place out that leaves a bad taste. No bartender should ever do that no matter which customer it is new or regular, never had this experience at another bar like this and all new customers please beware and think twice before going to this "great local place where everybody knows your name".', 'time': 1651195473}, {'author_name': 'Nicole Borress', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100811972162872172324/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GixM5IS60wu78fZ6Az06Z0VrHmTVjBNKZ8nZElquw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'A comfortable local bar, where everyone knows each other. It  was like a Guinness (with its cream foam top) with a hint of coconut taste. They do have freshly made popcorn (only "food" option) but did not try it.

There seemed to be only one bathroom, which was big and clean.

Veronica Tala and John make you feel like family', 'time': 1641509954}, {'author_name': 'Tala Haider', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108003690503147644226/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiRCz5NgD0_vO5sJsGMoUx7lxQ5yisxZw2HuccprQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '12 months ago', 'text': 'Ice cold beers, A/C on blast.
Baseball, hockey, basketball, football, soccer & horse racing. They do their best to put on what you want view. Most affordable bar in the neighborhood. Beers run $5-$6, shots $6-$7 , cocktails $6-7. They do buckets 5 beers for $25 Frozen drinks as well.
This bar has a neighborhood feel to it, lots of locals. Diversity amongst its patrons, different age groups and backgrounds, very welcoming. Juke box for music and the sound is spectacular. There is a back yard area with lights and seating for you to relax after a long day. This bars been around since the 1950’s and the iconic post time sign still bright at the window. They don’t serve food, like some of the reviews suggest, however they allow u to bring food in from outside in, an effort to support other local businesses outside. Bartenders are very attentive, friendly and make great drinks!
Dart board for recreation as well as various board games for entertainment.
Love this place', 'time': 1624919848}]

Name: The Rookery Bar
reviews:
[{'author_name': 'broccolli robb', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108666674681187159860/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgZbu1mCAc9X3pWIhWAmjSR-efJ9-WbZXksFHaJ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'in the last week', 'text': "As a member of the Burger king's club since 1992, I approve of the fries at the Rookery. They're steak cut, the best kind. The fried comes with a spicy, creamy sauce; however, I forget the name of it. We were welcomed by the bartender, Brian or Bryan; either way - great bartender.  On Monday nights they have $5 mussels, highly recommended. The drinks got us lit.  The place has a large front patio that can fit a large crowd.
OH and we finished off with fried oreos.", 'time': 1656424322}, {'author_name': 'Scott Benson', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105984809911154344123/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Ghw_uMtQmjeQK67u8G8snsULMLdRNbBq-IPz0CruA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '3 weeks ago', 'text': 'The Rookery has a wonderful rounded bar and a few booths as well as phenomenal outdoor seating for the warmer months.

With a great selection of bites and an even greater selection of whiskeys and the like. (Have an High West American Prairie or an Eagle Rare Single Barrel)

reviews:
[{'author_name': 'Mark Pincoski', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110649343811638309152/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgnLlbrMKxb2OPiXF7GjXmOX93ei3eYSFjGKbSp=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 weeks ago', 'text': "One of our most favorite places in the Finger Lakes region.  They have an outstanding selection of beer on tap...never a problem to find an old favorite or try something new.  Their selection of wines is a perfect balance of many area wineries.  And they have a full bar if that is your thing.  The food selection is not too extensive, but everything we've tried is always fantastic.  We've enjoyed the patio with it's beautiful view.  We always stop in when they have Friday night live music.  This is a must try for your next trip to the Finger Lakes.", 'time': 1655125937}, {'author_name': 'Ryan Lynch', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114580087727161402269/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GitqzpJapZIwaRYbcW4fXJ9JhBkaNdy8tM91L9s=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '4 weeks ago', 'text': 'My wife and I came in mainly for drinks, as advertised, and we stayed because of the experience. Alandis ("Lando") as our bartender was beyond amazing. He took great pride and excitement in making the various Old Fashions that it added to the whole experience. He even had a dedicated station at the bar just for making Old Fashions. The drinks themselves were fantastic, but the fact that they genuinely cared about the customers' reaction conveyed that extra level of involvement. We also ordered the Thai Lettuce Wraps and they had great taste and quality. Highly recommended for great drinks and food.', 'time': 1653884946}, {'author_name': 'steve wiedmaier', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116791617332067567436/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gj1zu0VSS-qn9wY-6ibcjogewbh9i81mdBUByXO2g=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'This is a beer bar, NOT a brewery!

reviews:
[{'author_name': 'Mark Edge', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110622457353565807688/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AATXAJzV4ey0dTunUQ4Ws8GM8fxUmkqrD_xGBKpWUpM4=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': "Great experience, i was at the old Inn several times but the new improvements make this small lake establishment a nice place get away to. Food was good and the service was great. A new bartender (first night) and she did great. Friendly environment, looking forward to the new boat docks being put in snd for summer time weather. Prices are high but this is not the Inn's doing, this is the effects of a government and their haphazard spending and not caring about the people they represent.", 'time': 1653692162}, {'author_name': 'Rosalinda Rice', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116436949214533655966/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AATXAJyq6FweF8i9_GFz3PBXkICnlNHg598lZ-1xI222=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '3 weeks ago', 'text': 'Nice friendly atmosphere. Clean, good service. Food was good but not anything special. Drinks were inexpensive.', 'time': 1654297562}, {'author_name': 'Rachel Taylor', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115988399767290868959/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Ggc_HmO-dIOGqu8QPQ7gW70q790mL5JNaRVEtKb=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': 'in the last week', 'text': 'I wish I could give it less than one star.  The wait and service is and was horrible.  We sat and waited for a table for 20 minutes without being acknowledged, now granted it was busy so I'm giving them a little slack.  Two of us ordered the fish fry, the wait was long as well for that.  The fish was overcooked and the Mac was fridge cold.  The wings were good and the burger was good.  The fries were mediocre.  We came again another night, trivia night, there were only three tables, one was pretty much done eating and receiving their check, the other playing trivia, and the last eating.  There were two waiters, one waiting and the other operating the trivia and serving since it was slow.  We waited for a about about 10-12 minutes and they saw us and didn't bother.  Then finally the waiter setting up trivia came and asked if we were looking to play the game, we say no, he says and I quote
"Okay bye!"
And doesn't seat us, or anything as if we didn't even exist.  It was a Tuesday night and slow, there was no reason for that at all.  I can name several things that would help this place out a lot and they are simple things.

This place is a great place if you are in absolutely no hurry at all and want appetizer type food.  It's not worth the price in my opinion, or the wait, and since it's a 50/50 shot on what your getting into honestly, it's not worth it.  I, almost,  prefer the old "Waneta Inn" compared to "The Boathouse".  Now "The Boathouse " is much cleaner and nicer, physically speaking, than the old one, I do give it credit there, that's about the only one up it has.

I hope this helps others, I'm not trying to be mean or nasty, I'm just being honest and this was very frustrating and heartbreaking for this place.  I hope they turn it around, or it'll go under just like "Waneta Inn".', 'time': 1655856623}, {'author_name': 'Patrick K', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103749671840985057592/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gg459bCasOF8si-1G9tcpuG6PzzSssd3lwDevSc=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': '2 weeks ago', 'text': 'Absolutely horrible. Prime rib ordered rare came out medium well. Wife was ill after eating some of it. Oriental noodle bowl tasted worse than a cheap frozen entre, barely ate a few bites of noodle, vegetable and chicken. Tossed out both leftovers. Ate peanut butter and jelly sandwich for dinner.', 'time': 1655204385}, {'author_name': 'Christine Hohman', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109291319500163195754/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gg9q4egJsgtx-FyY5bM4xecD3V_Ehhe_Cyla9DWZus=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '10 months ago', 'text': "Have been going to the Waneta all my life. reviews:

We ordered the calamari which were delicious and freshly fried, my husband had fish and chips and the fish was flaky and fresh, I ordered the club sandwich and that was amazing as well. I must say that they have one of the best fries we've tried! We also enjoyed an ice cream sundae and felt like kids again 😆

Name: Friends & Company Restaurant
reviews:
[{'author_name': 'Barbara Kauffman', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112339695729250866616/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AATXAJznYMOrfzxEURysUnWVkO9ukkNLd-bohPE_-u3R=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': "My husband & I are visiting Ct. from North Carolina. We decided to eat @ F&C. What a pleasant surprise. If you're looking for a  low key place to dine, this is it. They make their own bread. The food is fresh and wholesome. The service (Sara ) was attentive without being obtrusive. Light Jazz music playing in the background. They also display Art from local artist. CONGRATULATIONS TO THE OWNERS !!!", 'time': 1651840778}, {'author_name': 'Kelaino Hawkshawe', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117999268973891585838/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Ghu5AE01sn6feKq1f_zQtqjlHbtwLUhAmOOtUaJ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 2, 'relative_time_description': '2 months ago', 'text': "The quality of the food here is good, but its menu is very limited; it takes years for them to add new items to it. Also, the interior has a lot of dark wood and it has poor lighting, which give the place a tired, dated feeling. Good luck finding a diner there without white hair or silver hair--the average age of the customer base must be about 78.

This restaurant used to have a delicious twist on a grilled cheese--it was made with goat cheese and pesto, but unfortunately, they have removed it from the menu. They only have one type of burger, which is really basic. Compared to burgers I've had at other restaurants in this area, Friends & Co.'s burger is just OK.

If you are in the mood for a burger, I would suggest instead trying Haywire Burger Bar in Westbrook, or Jack Rabbit's in Old Saybrook. I ordered a traditional margarita and my date ordered a passionfruit one. When they first brought our drinks out they gave him a regular margarita and not a passion fruit one. After alerting the bartender they brought him out a new drink that still didn’t have any passion fruit in it. Rather than make a big fuss, we just proceeded to drink our drinks. I’m not sure what they served us but the drinks were not margaritas. It tasted almost like a seltzer beverage with some lemonade and I’m not so sure they even included alcohol in the drink. I’m a lightweight and I felt absolutely nothing after having my drink. Our server was MIA for most of the night and we were probably sitting there for around an hour before we were even able to put in an order for food. Then the food then took forever to come. When we did get our food, it was luke warm, not hot.

It’s such a shame that we received such poor service because this place has so much potential. It’s a nice cozy spot with a DJ, sports games, and they even have hookah. I do wish we had a better experience but the whole night was off. The staff seemed to be confused most of the night even though it wasn’t really busy. Name: Bask Bar & Grill
reviews:
[{'author_name': 'EE Grimshaw', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100309326164222941843/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gi1qplPUzbcST7McciVFt2KkACA55OKSMEoSiGkSK8=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 2, 'relative_time_description': '3 months ago', 'text': "I only go to sports bars once in a blue moon - usually for one March Madness game a year and a special, rare occasion like a Mets World Series game. Prior to the pandemic, my chum and I often went to 381 Main for those events. It wasn't the best in terms of food and overall quality, but it ultimately did what it was supposed to do, which is provide a decent sports viewing experience. It's really a shame they closed because their sibling Bask Bar & Grill is a significant step down.

The layout is just not comfortable - it's super narrow so it feels weird to try to roam around in just one little room (381 Main was probably twice the size if not more, and that's not even counting their larger patio/outdoor area), and I don't see a way that that can be fixed even by gutting some of the interior. It's just a small space in a mini strip mall that wasn't meant for a bar. Along with what you'd expect in a sports bar (some generic sports shizzle on the wall), the surfboard theme from 381 Main is here as well. I don't know that they necessarily complement each other, but I can't imagine anyone caring too much either way.

What really rubbed me the wrong way about this place was how they handled the kitchen. Both of us had skipped dinner with the intention of eating some bar food while we watched the game. Earlier in the day, we had gone online to research a 381 Main alternative and focused a great deal on the menu items of a few candidates. One of the main reasons we picked Bask was because the apps looked really good. When we got there to order, the bartender told us the kitchen was almost completely shut down and that we could only order a plain pizza - not even a pizza with meat on it or anything, just plain. That was really frustrating, especially because we had already checked Bask's website and social media pages and there weren't any references to the kitchen closing time, just a notation that they were open every day until 2am. To add insult to injury, we watched for the next 45 minutes as other peoples' apparently previously ordered food came out, so the kitchen WAS technically open. It just came off as disingenuous and disorganized. We settled for the plain pizza, which was okay (the crispy crust was the high point), but not what we wanted. If we had known the kitchen was pretty much closed, we wouldn't have come here, bottom line. It would have taken someone two minutes to update a website or Instagram/Facebook page with that information.

Another area where Bask doesn't match up to 381 Main is the drinks. I'm not the type of person who has a go-to cocktail order, so I usually rely on a cocktail menu if that's the direction I'm going in. The cocktail menu at 381 Main was pretty standard, with items like sangria, margaritas, etc., but this place didn't have a basic cocktail menu. (I'm sure most of the target audience for this bar doesn't care about this at all, so your mileage may vary.) On the fly, I asked for an Aperol spritz, which the bartender said they didn't have all the ingredients for, but that he could make something similar. Okay, fair enough. The drink was okay. Not particularly spritzy and it had a very faint cough syrup aftertaste but it honestly could have been worse.

The service was, again, okay. It didn't take too long to hail down the bartender for orders, but he never stopped by to follow up on drinks/food unless we motioned for him to come by. It's a sports bar so I don't think you should expect to be waited on hand and foot but there were definitely moments where he was just standing around and could have used that time to check in since it wasn't that crowded for most of the night. I probably would have ended up ordering an additional drink if he had been more proactive so that's money left on the table for them.

I'm sure it's possible to have a fine time here and there's an argument to be made that this just wasn't our scene - it was a crowd of mostly guys in their late 20s, early 30s. But I'll be looking for a different place to watch Gonzaga next year.", 'time': 1647859916}, {'author_name': 'Bruna DP', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114148069305359870849/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Ggqndpy90h8CNTGQx7UBBMfnRvHFsIu121-Novt6Yc=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '4 months ago', 'text': 'Best local spot winter spring summer fall 😊', 'time': 1645967456}, {'author_name': 'Franco', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104096037417388977990/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AATXAJyy51QpLaqtQHqirmuELqed7uRzg5L1Vzz4ES3x3bk=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '3 months ago', 'text': 'Great bar to have drinks and grub in the patio while watching a game', 'time': 1648409622}, {'author_name': 'Erin Dwyer', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113037626186639061178/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gh9Daz4z2FrqqlYGY_U6WE6CNMUV2zA89N5R6xY9Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 months ago', 'text': 'Cheese steak was the bomb and prices are very reasonable', 'time': 1648941411}, {'author_name': 'Hello There', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108753692603316755110/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AATXAJzkRBypungH4RlkZMGSq2Sk9ECpQGSdOPH_m18j=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '6 months ago', 'text': "Visited on Saturday. Name: Mud Hole
reviews: [{'author_name': 'Naresh Hinduja', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116040122370016978788/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhUeCIhOyZJ4xhr9We0-PPlqPzPsODZ7fIh5y2LMA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': '2 months ago', 'text': 'So I go through a lot of reviews saying their locals that go here etc. Good food, everybody\'s friendly etc. So I figured I\'d give it a try. I go in there. I ask for a somewhat expensive tequila bartender said it\'s $ 11.50 and I said that\'s fine because I understand it\'s that expensive. What I did not understand is after getting a small glass full of ice which was less than half full of the tequila that I paid $11.50 for made no sense. First of all, the glass is small So it stands to normal logical reasoning that after you fill ice if you put even just one full of shot, it should at least be half full. This was not even half full so I realized the bartender was just short-changing me now for a new customer that goes in and is willing to try a place out that leaves a bad taste. No bartender should ever do that no matter which customer it is new or regular, never had this experience at another bar like this and all new customers please beware and think twice before going to this "great local place where everybody knows your name".', 'time': 1651195473}, {'author_name': 'Nicole Borress', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100811972162872172324/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GixM5IS60wu78fZ6Az06Z0VrHmTVjBNKZ8nZElquw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '7 months ago', 'text': 'A comfortable local bar, where everyone knows each other. reviews: [{'author_name': 'maria mercaldi', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100451606339670035778/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AATXAJxN4jbobCgpB-R_0g2V1OEP5hdsb3lkk8De12Aj=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 2, 'relative_time_description': '3 months ago', 'text': "We stopped a Friday night during their Happy Hour . Would say the bar usually draws more of a 20s to 40 crowd but me at the ripe age of a young 57 feels comfortable there.. Music via jukebox is always playing there and usually appeals to me (leaning toward rock, alternative, punk - depending on the taste of whomever fed the internet based jukebox). Bartenders are friendly, attentive and drinks are reasonably priced. They do have food and do have a night menu too to satisfy your munchies after 10pm. It's not ritzy and I'm more of a low key and dive bar person anyway so this places is good for me. Try it!", 'time': 1647875041}]

reviews:
[{'author_name': 'Dawn Colbert', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108091186954915707191/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AATXAJxoxUWTF9EpyC3usUhR--FtfnAP3SwyeMJqTwsk=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '4 weeks ago', 'text': 'So yummy! I had a salmon Caesar salad, and my friend had a Cobb salad with chicken. She loved her sangria and I was happy with my house white.

It was clean, loved the atmosphere. Name: Nassau Bar
reviews: [{'author_name': 'Al Golzari', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102641063392588875134/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gj9XpxnQH9E2cFgM9p_o0hvkRWFCFGvFXHl91c=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '2 weeks ago', 'text': "Been living in the neighborhood since 2006 and found this little gem back in 2016 walking by one day.  Have no idea how I spent my first 10 years here not knowing about it.  Used to go now and again in 2016 and started coming back in 2021.  If you're a fan of down-to-earth dive bars that aren't pretentious, this is probably the bar for you.  The bartenders, day and night, are super friendly and definitely a sight for sore eyes.  I'm sorry to have seen a few awesome bartenders like Gigi leave but Phil, Kate, Vicki, Haley, Natalie, Grace are really great.  The owner is also a really nice guy and a lot more generous than other bars in the neighborhood.  My only complaints are that I wish there was one little signature snack that you can buy there (that they would bring from the outside)...like a soft pretzel or something.  But they allow outside food.  And I do wish that the tonic water had more bubbles and tasted a little fresher (sorry John).  But aside from those minor issues, this has become a great regular spot that I feel very welcomed at. reviews: [{'author_name': 'Philip Ambuel', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116451936796924487996/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiOoZ6wqo51AtekpjfEdSEr6qySDeb-mp00PnYZ3g=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': 'One of the best neighborhood bars. Never a dull moment! :)', 'time': 1650670195}, {'author_name': 'Rebecca Lynn', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101265175791268971210/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiBxKXKNx9alW2rztQk01ETm7lARMws0-XvsEdOgg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': '2 months ago', 'text': 'First time at this bar and bartender with dreads hospitality should be rated a -10. Trying to get his attention but to busy talking to “customers”then finally when my fiancé gets his attention he tells him “he had us until we mentioned margaritas” and to go to the other bartender who is now paying attention to people who showed up after us. Will never be returning again ever :)', 'time': 1650705395}, {'author_name': 'Demian Faunt', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107602610439516386977/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Ggz9ima90F6Xsi6Fo3Z0RU3dzjvosr-cZEzLB2dQg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': '2 months ago', 'text': 'Very chill watering hole in Bushwick. Good vibe and drinks were served quickly, albeit a little light on the booze. Great spot to chat and play pool.', 'time': 1649809695}, {'author_name': 'Shawn Henry', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111759685068114685644/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GhH9XnljmZ5HaLwyWrNTe01Nqil9bTZ-0DYipRh=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': '3 weeks ago', 'text': 'My friends threw an event there in the downstairs area the other night. Upon entering, two of my friends suggested taking shots and both offered their cards for the first two rounds. As they weren’t my cards, I didn’t tip the bartender and, on the second round, he became very sarcastic and disrespectful. When my turn to get the shots approached, I had full intention on tipping him out, but he immediately denied me service (rudely, at that), stating there was a “Three Strike” policy, in which I hadn’t yet violated (as this was my third turn.) I explained the situation, but he continued to be disrespectful, and eventually my friends got involved. In an attempt to de-escalate the situation, I approached the bar upstairs, ordered my shots, and tipped the bartender double the recommended amount. Heading back down, I handed them the shots, and showed the bartender that I had full intention on tipping him, even getting my friends to stop arguing with him. He then called security to escort me out, to which I complied without much fuss. I was not drunk - as my friend has already written a review in which your response tried to defame my character. If there is a problem, I have no problem showing up in person again to have a conversation, but I also have testimony that that was not that bartender’s first offense that night, as he tried to provoke one of my friends who was renting out the space for said event.', 'time': 1654384074}]
